## 💭 Retrospective

**Focus shift to design and validation.** Delegating repetitive and mechanical coding work to agents lets me concentrate on the 'lead engineer' role: designing architecture, reviewing logical integrity of agent outputs, and deciding what to build next.

**Exponential development velocity.** Complex refactors and boilerplate tasks that used to take days now take a single session. Product launch cycles shorten in proportion to how well the directive infrastructure is maintained.

**Consistent quality floor.** Agents enforce conventions and type checks at the infrastructure level that humans routinely miss under time pressure — code quality becomes a baseline, not a target to aim at.
